Nippon Steel Corp &lt;NSTC.T> and &lt;InlandSteel Co> of the U.S. Are negotiating to set up a joint steelventure in Indiana, a Nippon Steel spokesman said, declining togive more details.    Several local newspapers reported the joint venture wouldbe capitalised at 150 mln dlrs, owned 60 pct by Inland and 40pct by Nippon Steel, and have annual production capacity of onemln tonnes of steel to supply car makers. REUTER&#3;